- (10 + 2) × (10 − 3) = 12 × 7 = 84

We need to use **all four numbers**.

Try using division or subtraction cleverly.

(10 × 3) − (10 ÷ 2) = 30 − 5 = 25  
Close.

(10 + 2) × (3) − 10 = 12 × 3 − 10 = 36 − 10 = 26  
Still off.

(10 + 10) + (3 + 2) = 25  
(10 × 2) + (10 ÷ 2) = 20 + 5 = 25 — again 25.

Hmm.

Try:  
(10 − (3 − 2)) × something?
